algorithmSettings.name: seed
algorithmSettings.description: Integer seed for random number generator

measures.name: nrc_create_necb_prototype_building
measures.description: This measure creates an NECB prototype building from scratch and uses it as the base for an analysis.
measures.modeler_description:
This will replace the model object with a brand new model. It effectively ignores the seed model. If there are 
	updated tables/formulas to those in the standard they can be sideloaded into the standard definition - this new data will
	then be used to create the model.

arguments.name: sideload
arguments.display_name: Check for sideload files (to overwrite standards info)?

measures.name: openstudio_results
measures.description: This measure creates high level tables and charts pulling both from model inputs and EnergyPlus results. It has building level information as well as detail on space types, thermal zones, HVAC systems, envelope characteristics, and economics. Click the heading above a chart to view a table of the chart data.
measures.modeler_description: For the most part consumption data comes from the tabular EnergyPlus results, however there are a few requests added for time series results. Space type and loop details come from the OpenStudio model. The code for this is modular, making it easy to use as a template for your own custom reports. The structure of the report uses bootstrap, and the graphs use dimple js. The new measure warning section will show warnings generated by upstream measures. It will not show forward translation warnings, EnergyPlus warnings, or warnings that might be reported by this measure.

arguments.name: units
arguments.display_name: Which Unit System do you want to use?

arguments.name: reg_monthly_details
arguments.display_name: Report monthly fuel and enduse breakdown to registerValue
arguments.description: This argument does not effect HTML file, instead it makes data from individal cells of monthly tables avaiable for machine readable values in the resulting OpenStudio Workflow file.

measures.name: nrc_report_utility_costs
measures.description:
This measure calculates utility costs for Canadian locations. By default a simple $/kWh tarrif can be applied but for 
	    several locations more complex rules are enabled.
		Peak values are reported averaged over the hour (the default LEED table produced by E+ reports the PEAK timestep value).
measures.modeler_description: The measure creates a simple csv file and html output. The annual costs are available as output metrics for PAT.
